            class="- topic/topic concept/concept ">
		    <title class="- topic/title ">
			      <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">6.301</ph> Policy.</title>
		    <conbody class="- topic/body concept/conbody ">
			      <ol id="d378e13" class="- topic/ol ">
				        <li class="- topic/li ">
					          <p id="d385e17" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(a)</ph>
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
						            
						            <xref href="http://uscode.house.gov/browse.xhtml;jsessionid=114A3287C7B3359E597506A31FC855B3"
                        format="html"
                        scope="external"
                        class="- topic/xref ">41 U.S.C.3304</xref> and <xref href="http://uscode.house.gov/browse.xhtml;jsessionid=114A3287C7B3359E597506A31FC855B3"
                        format="html"
                        scope="external"
                        class="- topic/xref ">10 U.S.C.2304(c)</xref> each authorize, under certain conditions, contracting without providing for full and open competition. The Department of Defense, Coast Guard, and <ph class="- topic/ph ">National Aeronautics and Space Administration are subject to </ph>
						            <xref href="http://uscode.house.gov/browse.xhtml;jsessionid=114A3287C7B3359E597506A31FC855B3"
                        format="html"
                        scope="external"
                        class="- topic/xref ">10 U.S.C.2304(c)</xref>. Other executive agencies are subject to <xref href="http://uscode.house.gov/browse.xhtml;jsessionid=114A3287C7B3359E597506A31FC855B3"
                        format="html"
                        scope="external"
                        class="- topic/xref ">41 U.S.C.3304</xref>. Contracting without providing for full and open competition or full and open competition after exclusion of sources is a violation of statute, unless permitted by one of the exceptions in <xref href="FAR-i1119460.dita#i1119460"
                        base="i1119460"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        class="- topic/xref ">6.302</xref>.</p>
				        </li>
				        <li class="- topic/li ">
					          <p id="d385e45" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(b)</ph>
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
						            Each contract awarded without providing for full and open competition shall contain a reference to the specific authority under which it was so awarded. Contracting officers shall use the U.S. Code citation applicable to their agency. (See <xref href="FAR-i1119460.dita#i1119460"
                        base="i1119460"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        class="- topic/xref ">6.302</xref>.)</p>
				        </li>
				        <li class="- topic/li ">
					          <p id="d385e57" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(c)</ph>
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
						            Contracting without providing for full and open competition shall not be justified on the basis of-</p>
					          <ol id="d378e60" class="- topic/ol ">
						            <li class="- topic/li ">
							              <p id="d385e67" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(1)</ph>
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
								                A lack of advance planning by the requiring activity; or</p>
						            </li>
						            <li class="- topic/li ">
							              <p id="d385e76" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(2)</ph>
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
								                Concerns related to the amount of funds available (<i class="+ topic/ph hi-d/i ">e.g.,</i> funds will expire) to the agency or activity for the acquisition of supplies or services.</p>
						            </li>
					          </ol>
				        </li>
				        <li class="- topic/li ">
					          <p id="d385e90" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(d)</ph>
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
						            When not providing for full and open competition, the contracting officer shall solicit offers from as many potential sources as is practicable under the circumstances.</p>
				        </li>
				        <li class="- topic/li ">
					          <p id="d385e99" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(e)</ph>
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
						            For contracts under this subpart, the contracting officer shall use the contracting procedures prescribed in <xref href="FAR-i1120068.dita#i1120068"
                        base="i1120068"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        class="- topic/xref ">6.102</xref>(a) or (b), if appropriate, or any other procedures authorized by this regulation.</p>
				        </li>
			      </ol>
		    </conbody>
